    Baga Beach - Fun
    I visited Goa with my friends and we stayed at a hotel very near to Baga beach. This beach attracts hordes of tourists, and as we arrived, we immediately felt the electrifying atmosphere in the air. Baga Beach offers the perfect balance of relaxation and entertainment, with its golden sands and perfectly safe swimming waters. We indulged in thrilling water sports during the day, from parasailing to jet-skiing. The rates are negotiable so you have to bargain. As the sun set, the beach transformed into a hub of nightlife. Lined with charming shacks, it was the ideal spot to savor delicious seafood and dance the night away. Baga Beach truly captures the essence of Goa's vibrant spirit.
    Visited May 2023
    Travelled with friends

  • Avilash Singh
    New Delhi, India8 contributions
    An evening at Baga Beach
    To enjoy Baga Beach in Goa with friends, you should block your evening. Baga Beach has the vibe of loud music (Hindi and Punjabi mostly), drinks and relaxation. I went there in two evenings to enjoy the shack and relax when the table was close to the water. The breeze was amazing and the food was best. I was with one of my friends who had never been to Goa before, however, this was my 5th time going to Goa. I convinced my friend to go and relax rather than ticking all the famous spots. Hence, I was aware that the best location to relax (drinks and food) and good vibe is Baga Beach. I recently got interested in staying in hostels so I booked 2 beds in a 4-bed room in a hostel near Candolim. We reached the hostel around 2 PM, dropped our bags and then left to rent a Scooty. We straight headed towards Baga Beach and enjoyed the sunset first. Just before it got dark, we decided to sit in front of the shack and spent 5-6 hrs there. We ordered starter food and drinks, and after some time ordered Hookah as well. We both are not addicted to drink and smoking, but Socially and especially Baga Beach at Goa was giving us the vibe to do so. Small vendors coming by, and tourist people were crossing in front of us all the time which made me a little uncomfortable. However, all the shacks were the same so it was normal and people who were walking were also normal including some kids. The name of the shack was something "Paradise", not so classy but the service of food and drinks was good. If you went there and could not find a spot to sit, you can give a try to them. That's all in the blog if you have any questions or looking for some suggestions. I am happy to answer.
    Visited September 2023

Pune, India2,989 contributions
Best Nightlife is Goa seashore
Jul 2023 • Family
1. Baga Beach is one of the most happening beach in North Goa. Even in night you can enjoy the shore with drinks and food on shakes/chairs and feet in cold sand.
2. In the evening baga beach looks like heaven, perfect place to take DP and enjoy nightlife after that. Shakes are present but now a days they are very expensive. You can have meal, massage, tattoo all on shakes. However all these are bit expensive, specially tattoo.
3. Just beside calangute beach, one can easily access sports activities and you have ample hotels to provide food and drinks in both baga and calangute beach.
4. I would highly recommend to buy t-shirt for all which has ‘visit goa’ or ‘goa’
5. We bought the laser gun and my son played the laser game with other laser guys on the beach.
6. It can be hot during afternoon but night is pleasant.
7. Paid parking is available and for washroom sometimes you have to walk a bit.
8. It is safe with kids also as waves are not that strong. However take care of your kids.
9. One can also go for dolphin spotting tours and island trips from the beach.
Written 24 June 2024

I have planned to travel to goa from Mumbai on 11 the night by train. And planning to stay there upto 16 th . Is it safe to visit at present rainy season during my stay.
Written 8 August 2019
SmittenWithLife ✨
New Delhi, India
437 contributions
I came back from Goa yesterday. Last week, it rained almost all day. We did not have 1 complete hr when it did not rain. So, if you are visiting next week (and after seeing the weather forecast which is more or less same as compared to previous week)- do keep a nice raincoat and umbrella with you (in Goa, you can get cheap raincoats but those are not good). Plus, in goa there is a cab strike going on so you may not find cab to travel. There are some govt. approved taxi service which is available via “Goa miles” only and it is difficult to get cab due to high requests. For tour-You can rent a car if you know how to drive. Avoid renting a scooty or bike due to showers. We couldn’t enjoy full due to rain; other than that, Goa is lush green these days.
